<br>
We wanted pets to be immune to fear, and we got it.  It's a gimpy spell that doesn't last long enough, but we got it.<br>
<br>
We asked for pet SOW.  We got pet JBoot speed, but for some strange reason pet SOW is one of the rarest drops and there's more reasons to not cast it than to cast it.<br>
<br>
We asked for pets to not eat a wave of rains, which is really handy in PvP and made mages more welcome in AE groups.  I very rarely see AE groups so again, it's hardly an issue.<br>
<br>
Improved mod rod!  Wooo.  I never envied the necro's ability to give all his mana to other people.  That ability sucks.  Having a good use for your own mana would be a lot cooler.<br>
<br>
We got pet heals.  So... Quick trivia quiz.  Would you rather:<br>
A) Spend 400 mana to heal your pet for 900 hit points or<br>
B) Spend 400 mana to summon a new Greater Voceration pet for 2800 hit points?<br>
<br>
The heals are a red herring.  Distracting, but not that useful.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Basically we asked for meat and potatoes and we got a couple of cookies, a pat on the head and a point towards the door.  How about 1 nuke with Lure style resist rates?  How about upgrading pet melee damage across the board to reflect the MASSIVE increases to player melee damage since the game came out?  How about better alternate skills than these halftime elemental forms?  How about letting pre-epic mages be damage dealers like we were pre-Kunark?<br>
<br>
I made my mage after leveling a warrior to 58.  Frankly, warriors got spoiled.  My damage output jumped bigtime with Kunark and then again with Velious.  Skills like Defensive made me a solid #1 tank.  Those were some real, big time, heavy hitting, serious enhancements.<br>
<br>
What did YOU get?  Pets they won't let you summon in raids, a COTH spell and a greater ability to give your mana to people who can cast REAL spells?<br>
<br>
