<br>
Wizards are obviously #1 in the short term, but they run out of juice.  My point is that mages used to be invited to groups as a primary damage dealer, and now they're not, and IMO changing from &quot;damage dealer&quot; to &quot;utility/TV watcher&quot; is not an improvement on the class.  You can talk about old dogs and new tricks, but maybe the dog doesn't WANT to play dead.<br>
<br>
And really, I'd say we're the #3 debuffer.  That's #3 of 3.<br>
#1: Shaman.  Resist debuffs, de-hastes, other debuffs.<br>
#2: Enchanter.  Inferior (but stackable!) resist debuff, inferior de-hastes, other debuffs, mana drains.<br>
#3: Mage.  Resist debuffs.<br>
<br>
So I'd say we're pretty well dead last, out of the classes who are actually expected to cast debuffs.  You can say how you supplement the shaman, but really, if there were an extra shaman instead of the mage, the mage wouldn't be missed at all unless COTH was needed.<br>
